<item>
            <title>[LU-18719] make the error message of &quot;lfs setquota&quot; to be more meaningful</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18719</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The error message of &quot;lfs setquota is not meaningful sometimes, e.g.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;# lfs setquota -u usr2341 -i 16000000 /lustre/client/
# lfs setquota -u usr2341 -I 15000000 /lustre/client/
lfs setquota: quotactl failed: Invalid argument
setquota failed: Invalid argument
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It should be more meaningful &quot;the SoftLimit can&apos;t be larger than the HardLimit&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
